# Project defaults (example)

Copy relevant lines into your project's CLAUDE.md. This file is loaded
frequently, so keep it short.

## Skills

- Bootstrap a new repository with `oss-bootstrap`.
- Plan with `oss-plan` before substantial code.
- Build with `implement-minimal`.
- Diagnose failing tests or builds with `test-and-debug`.
- Gate new dependencies with `dependency-review`.
- Audit task fidelity with `implementation-integrity` after debugging.
- Review with `public-code-review` before merging.
- Gate publishing and deployment with `release-deploy`.

## Defaults

- No speculative abstractions.
- No comments that narrate obvious code.
- No unrelated refactoring or formatting churn.
- Truthful documentation only; no fabricated tests, metrics, or claims.
- Run targeted validation first; full validation only at milestones.
- Follow low-resource execution (see `.claude/shared/LOW_RESOURCE.md`).
- Never overwrite files silently.
- Report exactly what was and was not validated.

## Context efficiency

See `.claude/shared/CONTEXT_EFFICIENCY.md`.

- Select files before reading.
- Prefer targeted search and bounded ranges.
- Do not preload all references.
- Avoid rereading unchanged files.
- Finish one increment before expanding scope.
- Create a compact handoff when context is low.
